===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|bat-pro|lv}} {{m|ine-bsl-pro|*irā}} ([[cf]]. dialectal, archaic forms {{m|lv|irād}}, {{m|lv|iraid}}, {{m|lv|irāg}}, and also {{cog|lt|yrà}}, which existed alongside {{m|ine-pro|*esti}} ([[cf]]. {{cog|cu|єстъ|tr=jestŭ}}, {{cog|ru|есть|tr=jest’}}, {{etyl|lt|-}} dialectal {{m|lt|ẽsti}}, {{cog|prg|ast}}), initially with basically existential (“there is”) meaning, but later on extending to all copular meanings, thus replacing {{m|ine-pro|*esti}}. In {{etyl|xsv|-}}, also the first person form {{m|xsv|irm||I am}} is derived from this stem. The origin of {{cog|bat-pro|*irā}} is, however, unclear. Various sources have been proposed: an older interjection ([[cf]]. {{cog|lt|aurè||look!}}), the particle and conjunction {{m|lv|ir||both... and...}}, a noun with the meaning “existence,” “reality,” “thing,” or even (more recently) the {{etyl|ine-pro|-}} secondary third-person verbal ending {{m|ine-pro|*-r}} with a later ''-ā''-extension.<ref name="LEV">{{R:lv:LEV}}</ref>

